<statement><div><p>A car traveling at <m>{120}</m> m/s brakes uniformly and comes to rest in <m>{10}</m> seconds.</p>

<p>a) What is its deceleration?<br/>
Deceleration = <fillin characters="6" name="ans1"/> m/s²  </p>

<p>b) How far does it travel before stopping?<br/>
Stopping distance = <fillin characters="6" name="ans2"/> m  </p></div></statement>
<solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>
<p>Given: <m> u = {120} </m> m/s, <m> v = 0 </m> m/s, <m> t = {10} </m> s</p>

<p><alert>Part (a): Deceleration </alert><br/></p><p/>
<md>
<mrow>a =\amp  \frac{v - u}{t}</mrow>
<mrow>\ =\amp  \frac{0 - {120}}{10}</mrow>
<mrow>=\amp  {-12}\,\, \text{m/s²}</mrow>
</md> <br/>
(negative indicates deceleration)

<p><alert>Part (b): Distance travelled before stopping</alert><br/>
<md>
<mrow>s \amp = \frac{u + v}{2} \times t</mrow>
<mrow>\amp = \frac{{120} + 0}{2} \times {10}</mrow>
<mrow>\amp ={600}\,\, \text{m}</mrow>
</md> </p></div></solution>
<answer><p><m>-12</m></p></answer>
<answer><p><m>600</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>